		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Who said &quot;modern&quot;?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- I want cartridges back for sale in stores! Yes, I'm nostalgic and would love to see my old times back again as "normal business". Who said "modern" is the best gaming experience? Who said that "Wiimote" is better than a NES controller? Who said that "Resident Evil 4 Wii" is better than Mega Man II? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />
<br />
<br />- The big Nintendo could release a retro-console, with cartridges. I would prefer NES-style (top loading) instead of a SuperNES-style. Think about buying a new cartridge, playing it for a couple of hours, take it out and feel the hot case... wonderful.
<br />
<br />- At the beginning, the Neo Geo CD was marked "slow" due to the CD drive and its loading times. Later, the Nintendo64 was marked "retro" due to the high cost production of cartridges and much less space to store a game. The example is Mega Man Legends.
<br />
<br />- Can you think about Capcom releasing a new NES Mega Man, with new graphics, extra channels for its sound and so on? Well, I'm saying "Mega Man" because it's my best, plus a game that you play over and over again without losing gaming value. Actually, most of the modern games have no replay value when you beat it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


