	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Are N64 games not "game paks"?</div>
<br />Nintendo 64 and GBA Game Paks use a seek/read architecture, but the interface can seek to any byte address, not just 512-byte boundaries like on CF cards, SD cards, and DS Game Cards, and seeking has sub-microsecond latency, unlike on some CF and SD cards.
<br />
<br />Any NES Game Pak more complicated than NROM has "glue logic".

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


